Abstract

We present a numerical simulation of 10,000,000 independently initialized quantum wavepackets evolving under a shared curvature potential with no interaction Hamiltonian.
Standard many-body theory predicts that such a system should remain uncorrelated indefinitely, as no two-body coupling terms exist.



Instead, the system undergoes spontaneous macroscopic fusion, producing:



A single composite peak formed from all 10â· wavefunctions
A sigmoid-shaped coherence order-parameter indicating a phase transition
